application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the Provider Mobile App in the Virtual Practice?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Provider Mobile App is the iOS and Android companion to the Virtual Practice platform. It allows doctors and healthcare providers to manage consultations, capture AI-powered notes, review patient charts, and communicate securely with patients while on the go."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does the Provider App include full practice administration?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. Full configuration and administration features are available in the Virtual Practice Manager (web interface). The Provider App focuses on what providers need most: consultations, patient management, records access, secure messaging, and AI-powered documentation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I use AI Scribe from the mobile app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The Provider App includes the AI Scribe feature so you can dictate encounters or capture ambient conversations and have them converted into structured consultation notes, directly from your phone or tablet."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What types of consultations can providers manage in the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The app supports multiple consultation types:\n\nVideo visits for telehealth\n\nText consults for asynchronous communication\n\nIn-person visit support for documenting office encounters\n\nRemote monitoring for reviewing patient-generated health data and alerts"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is the Provider App more secure than texting patients directly?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Unlike SMS, WhatsApp, or personal calls, the Provider App uses encrypted, HIPAA-appropriate messaging that keeps PHI safe, protects your personal phone number, and creates an auditable record of patient communications."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"